n\\\" in agent guidance with a note that no environment or system properties are needed, ensuring tests target the jakarta.activation package and not the old javax.activation. This shouldn't require any additional setup. However, if they’re looking for only setup advice, I need to decide if the deterministic setup should be listed as none.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra dependency, Docker image, environment variable, or system property is required. The resolved jakarta.activation-api:2.0.0 artifact has no Maven dependencies and contains the jakarta.activation classes needed for meaningful unit coverage; the observed javac failure is from legacy javax.activation imports in existing 1.2.1 tests after the Jakarta package rename.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment or system property setup is needed. Generated tests for 2.0.0 should import and exercise jakarta.activation.* classes, not javax.activation.*. Useful coverage can target DataHandler/DataSource, FileTypeMap/MimetypesFileTypeMap, MailcapCommandMap/CommandInfo, and in-test command/content-handler classes without external services.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Current project documentation notes the API implementation later moved to Eclipse Angus; however, the 2.0.0 artifact itself contains the activation classes and has no declared dependencies, so adding Angus is not justified unless local verification exposes a concrete missing implementation path.\",\n    \"Existing metadata for 1.2.1 allows javax.activation; version 2.0.0 coverage and metadata likely need the jakarta.activation namespace instead.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0921ad4db5af94c0016a40ce79f9948197a019ef7414a99496\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1003, "output": 785, "cacheRead": 15872, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 17660, "cost": {"input